verbose_text: Innate immune functions are stimulated also by IGF-I : in vitro administration of salmon IGF-I, human IGF-I, and IGF-II increased superoxide production in zymosan stimulated rainbow trout head kidney leukocytes, and salmon IGF-I had a significant effect on superoxide production, which was observed to be equipotent to that of salmon GH [XREF_BIBR].
